# Architecture Documentation Format

When working with any file that has 'architecture', 'arch', or 'design' in the filename, format the document according to the following guidelines:

## Overview
- Provide a high-level summary of the architecture
- Include a system context diagram
- List key architectural principles and patterns

## Component Architecture
- Document major components and their responsibilities
- Define interfaces between components
- Describe data flows and dependencies

## Technical Decisions
- Document key technical decisions with rationales
- Include alternatives considered
- Provide decision contexts and constraints

## Data Model
- Describe core entities and relationships
- Include schema information or ER diagrams
- Document data flow and storage strategies

## Non-Functional Requirements
- Security considerations
- Scalability approach
- Performance targets
- Reliability and resilience patterns

## Implementation Notes
- Technology stack details
- Development environment setup
- Build and deployment pipeline

## Future Considerations
- Known limitations
- Evolution path
- Technical debt items